headline: Innodata Shares Surge After Palantir Deal. Stay Bullish.
summary: Innodata  stock rose sharply on Thursday following the announcement that it had been selected by  Palantir Technologies  to provide training data and annotation capabilities.  A Barron’s stock pick, Innodata has returned 73% from our call in September 2025, including a 25% rally thus far this year to a recent price of $63.58.  Landing Palantir as a customer is a major win for Innodata, further validating its technical expertise and leadership in AI training solutions.
